  "prompt": "Do Japanese like Indian food?",
  "response": "Japanese people's perception of Indian food varies, but there is growing interest and appreciation for Indian cuisine in Japan. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Popularity of Curry\n- Japanese curry is very popular, though different from authentic Indian curry\n- Many Japanese enjoy authentic Indian curry as well\n- Indian-style curry restaurants are becoming more common in major cities\n\n2. Growing Interest\n- Increasing number of Indian restaurants in Japan, especially in Tokyo and other large cities\n- Some Japanese people appreciate the spicy and flavorful nature of Indian cuisine\n- Younger generations are more adventurous in trying international foods\n\n3. Challenges\n- Traditional Japanese cuisine is mild, so some people find Indian food too spicy\n- Some may need time to adjust to strong spices and flavors\n- Cost of authentic Indian ingredients can be high in Japan\n\n4. Cultural Exchange\n- Cultural exchanges and increased global awareness have made Japanese more open to Indian food\n- Indian restaurants often adapt their dishes to suit Japanese taste preferences\n\n5. Demographic Factors\n- Urban areas and younger generations tend to be more receptive to Indian cuisine\n- People who have traveled or studied abroad are often more interested in international foods\n\nOverall, while not universally loved, Indian food is gaining popularity and appreciation in Japan.",
